  "text": "People communicate with each other by exchanging verbal and visual expressions. However, paralyzed patients with various neurological diseases such as amyotrophic lateral sclerosis and cerebral ischemia have difficulties in daily communications because they cannot control their body voluntarily. In this context, brain-computer interface (BCI) has been studied as a tool of communication for these types of patients. BCI is a computer-aided control technology based on brain activity data such as EEG, which is appropriate for BCI systems because of its noninvasive nature and convenience of recording [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
